Utica, Mich., Nov. 22, 1892;
Dear Mary + Anna; Aunts:-
As it is not possible for us to materialize on Thanksgiving at your house, we are doing the next most pleasant thing and sending you all greetings by mail. I think we all have great reason for gratitude to Our Heavenly Father for his kind care over us. How wonderfully we are sustained day after day.
